# Public repo hygiene (Conductor maintainers)

Conductor is **public OSS**. Tracked files must **never** name Vault & Compass portfolio
products, private application repos, or links to private downstream PRs.

## Never put in git

- Portfolio app codenames or customer-facing product brands
- `github.com/vaultcompasshq/<private-app>` PR/issue links
- Dogfood notes that identify which private repo supplied a prompt
- Session handoffs, audits, or week-ahead plans (use gitignored `.local/` or `TODO.local.md`)

## Write instead

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Named product + PR link | "private Tier 0 app repo", "downstream integration PR" |
| App-branded validation filenames | `tier0-extraction-….md`, `tier0-cursor-integration-….md` |
| Replay tests titled with product + PR | `onboarding replay: integration-link path …` |
| Same token in prohibition **and** test path | e.g. don't pair "vendor production credentials" with `vendor-link-button.tsx` |

## Before commit or PR

```bash
pnpm validate:portfolio-names
```

CI runs this on every PR. Policy: [docs/release/public-content-policy.md](../../docs/release/public-content-policy.md).

## Install locally

```bash
mkdir -p .cursor/rules
cp integrations/cursor/no-portfolio-names.mdc .cursor/rules/no-portfolio-names.mdc
```
